Text:
Hello, good day to you. I am Charles Citrine, you may call me Mr. Citrine. My name is Charles Citrine, Mr Citrine to you. I hope this won't take long.

 How old am I, doesn't it say on your record?

I hope this won't take long.

 How old am I, doesn't it say on your record? I was born in 1995 so I am about thirty. I just gave my date of birth to your receptionist so they should have have it, I was born on the 29th February 1995.

 Reason for visit.

I just gave my date of birth to your receptionist so they should have have it, I was born on the 29th February 1995.

 Reason for visit. I am here because I have noticed occasionally that my vision is uncomfortable because of glare. Particularly when I'm driving, headlights bother me. Its car headlights that are the real problem for me, lots of glare at night when I'm driving.

Particularly when I'm driving, headlights bother me. Its car headlights that are the real problem for me, lots of glare at night when I'm driving. I have noticed the glare for many years and only recently have I thought to do anything about it. It has not got significantly worse lately. 

 My distance vision and near vision are generally good.

It has not got significantly worse lately. 

 My distance vision and near vision are generally good. I generally see very well - my focus is fine. I don't wear glasses at the moment, this is the first time I've been a patient in an optician's practice. So this is all new to me.

I don't wear glasses at the moment, this is the first time I've been a patient in an optician's practice. So this is all new to me. I haven't had a sight test before.

 Other symptoms. Other than the glare, I don't have any problems with my eyes or vision.

Other symptoms. Other than the glare, I don't have any problems with my eyes or vision. They aren't painful or red or sore or anything like that. I don't notice flashes of light in my eyes. I don't notice floating specks in my vision.

I don't notice flashes of light in my eyes. I don't notice floating specks in my vision. I don't get floaters in my vision. I don't get double vision.

 My ocular history and previous eye problems.

I don't get double vision.

 My ocular history and previous eye problems. I have never had to visit the hospital as a patient for my eyes in the past. I don't get headaches usually but if I've been sat in front of a screen all day I do sometimes get a headache, mostly due to posture though; I suspect. 

 Family ocular history.

I don't get headaches usually but if I've been sat in front of a screen all day I do sometimes get a headache, mostly due to posture though; I suspect. 

 Family ocular history. There is a history of cataract in the family. My brother and sisters have them, and my mother does. All of them were born with them, which I gather is unusual.

My brother and sisters have them, and my mother does. All of them were born with them, which I gather is unusual. Nevertheless it doesn't seem to prevent them from doing anything they want to.

 Family medical history, family health. My family has generally good health and no-one takes medicines for anything regularly.

 My general health is good. I don't smoke. I don't really drink alcohol, except the odd glass of excellent wine.

I don't smoke. I don't really drink alcohol, except the odd glass of excellent wine. I don't have diabetes or any other systemic condition. 

 My medication. I don't take medicines for anything.

My medication. I don't take medicines for anything. 

 Screen use, computers. I use a screen a lot for work, at least eight hours a day. 

 Occupation, work, for a living.

I use a screen a lot for work, at least eight hours a day. 

 Occupation, work, for a living. I work as a clinical negligence solicitor, mostly working to get people compensation from when their opticians get things wrong. I know that lots of opticians miss things out, so I'm always keen to make sure that I ruin their lives for making mistakes. I expect everything to be perfect, just as my legal cases are and I enjoy finding things wrong in record cards.

 Outside of work, I do have some hobbies, in my spare time. I like my classic cars. I have a 1969 MGB which has a failing carburettor at present.

 I also like wines, and when I do drink it's always a nice Australian shiraz. There are some good vintages out there, for the right price.

Hobbies yes, I enjoy bluegrass music, and have in the past played the mandolin. I enjoy cinema, particularly Italian cinema of the 1970s. There are some tremendous films from that era.
